nsaudit: /tests/nsaudit-fixtures/minimal (role=toplevel, nodevs=unset, actid=-1, xenith=0)

authorities
  attaches_device
  writes_fs_durable
  execs_code
  spawns_proc
  writes_fs
  reads_fs

reads_fs
  /n/local/Users/pdfinn/sample
  /tmp/veltro
  /lib/certs
  /dev/time
  /dev/null
  /dev/cons
  /dis/veltro
  /dis/lib

writes_fs
  /tmp/veltro [ephemeral]
  /n/local/Users/pdfinn/sample [DURABLE]

violations
  [medium] DURABLE_HOST_MUTATION
    Caps grant writes to durable host paths (not /tmp/veltro, not cowfs-staged). Changes persist on the host with no revert path.
    fix: enable cowfs (actid >= 0) for these paths, or narrow caps.paths to /tmp/veltro
  [high] UNCONSTRAINED_SHELL
    exec is granted with no caps.shellcmds allowlist. The spawned shell can run any command reachable in the agent namespace; nothing narrows it.
    fix: set caps.shellcmds to the minimal command set, or remove exec
  [high] DEVICE_GATE_BYPASS
    top-level caps grants kernel device attach without NODEVS. Any sys->bind on an #x device will succeed, reaching #sfactotum, #U (host fs), or other kernel services regardless of path-based restriction.
    fix: add sys->pctl(Sys->NODEVS, nil) after the FORKNS site
  [info] EXEC_FORCE_MULTIPLIER
    exec in caps.tools. All other authority limits are soft because the spawned shell can re-invoke anything in the agent namespace. Pair with caps.shellcmds to narrow.
    fix: remove exec if not needed, or constrain via caps.shellcmds
  [high] EXFIL_RISK_EGRESS
    Any file the agent can read can leave the machine via the egress path listed. Reads plus egress is exfiltration risk.
    fix: remove egress, narrow reads_fs to a non-sensitive set, or narrow caps.shellcmds
